In 2012 I moved to Park City, Utah, from country Victoria in Australia to be with @alexgelsomino. At that time I had never been to USA before and never been to the snow! I was so nervous, but @kblock43 & @mrslucyjonesblock were so kind and caring to me and made me feel at home. The following year my brother @brendorally and I rallied in the Rally America Championship and I got this great photo! I still remember the excitement that all 4 of us were racing. Getting out and doing something @kblock43 loved, was a good way to put some smiles back on our faces last night, in these extremely difficult times and pay tribute to the great man. It’s important we continue to love racing and the feeling it gives us! @alexgelsomino & I will stick to co-driving, as when you go karting @gridexperience with the Block’s and @travispastrana, your names sit at the bottom of the times!!

In 2018 my brother @brendorally & I were gravel crew/safety crew at WRC Spain for @kblock43 & @alexgelsomino! We were excited to be given this responsibility. Ken Block's first-ever car livery was snow-camo with gold DC logos, which ran on his Subaru STI rally car for the 2005 season and the modified road car he used in the Gumball 3000. One of our favorite photo shoots were those two cars in front of a Vermont maple syrup sugar shack. That livery was the start of something special and helped set in motion a motorsports career that would change automotive culture and impact so many people.

We wanted to pay tribute to Ken in a meaningful way, so ahead of this weekend’s Nitro RX event in Quebec we've wrapped Travis Pastrana’s Group E car in that now iconic snow-camo to celebrate Ken and all that he accomplished. 

Rally in Paradise, Ken. #kb43ver #gonitro #nitrorx 

📸: Lars Gange and @matthew.stryker

Long story short…I am not posting this for pity, but just to show the body is an incredible and fascinating thing and I wanted to share. 

Because I like to run, my doctor wanted to get new leg X-rays to check out how things were looking from my rally crash in 2009, where both my legs were broken. Just checking for arthritis etc. 

If you were not aware, I broke right femur 2 places, right tib and fib 2 places, left femur 2 places and left heel. Plus compartments syndrome in the right lower leg. I had rods/pins/screws through both femurs (now removed) and through my right tibia (now removed). My right fibula was left broken, as the main concern was to save my life. The fibula is a non weight bearing bone. So you can technically live with it broken, like I do. 

So now after 13 years and 11 surgeries, check out my left femur size (nearly double the thickness) and my broken right tibia (still trying to work out how to connect).

If you don’t know who this lady is… you should. Michele Mouton is the only woman to ever win rounds of the @officialwrc as a driver. She took four victories and finished runner-up in the drivers world championship in 1982. David Evans of @dirtfishrally described her as "motorsport's most successful ever female driver". A brilliant documentary, called Queen of Speed (can be found on YouTube) documents Mouton's rise to the top of rallying in the 1980s and was awarded an Emmy for the Best Sports Documentary at the 50th International Emmy Awards in 2022! A true role model and legend! Thank you @josierimmer_ from @dirtfishrally for bringing Michèle out to USA, for so many fans to enjoy her stories and knowledge over the weekend at the @dirtfishrally Women in Motorsport Summit. What an incredible opportunity for me to sit alongside Michèle on this panel 💯

Keeping motivated to exercise, isn’t always easy when you are busy! Unfortunately the last few months I have been on the road a lot and struggling to find the time for enough sleep, let alone time to train. Anyone else struggle with this? But I know training keeps my body and mind healthy. So I have to set parameters which allow for both my work and fitness goals to be achieved. I am home now 8 days and have no excuses. Yesterday I rode 1h and today I ran/hiked 1h. I aim to do a minimum 1h exercise the days I am home and 30m the days I am away. No excuses. This is achievable and will keep me on track for my fitness and mind! #getoutside #getmoving @ozrallypro @blackriflecoffee @blackriflecoffeepink @brcc_fit

Off to @dirtfishrally! What an incredible photo 📸 @aaronkathman from @oregontrailrally! New Zealand - Co-driver Development Training 

After the overwhelming response to our @ozrallypro Group Co-driver Courses in Australia, I am excited to offer our first trainings in New Zealand since 2019. 

The trainings will be a one day program, held on Saturday August 5th and Sunday August 6th from 9am - 5pm at Rally New Zealand HQ - Mt Richmond Domain - Auckland. 

The training is $450NZD each and is available for up to 12 students per day. This course caters to any level of experience, but is more aimed at novice competitors and co-drivers looking for further develop their skills. 

Please refer to below for more details. 

If you would like to book your spot or have further questions, please email ozrallypro@gmail.com.

No age limit. This class has had 12 year olds participate in the past.
Thanks @speedcafe @torquecafe for the story! Appreciate the support from my home country 🇦🇺 Click on link in bio to read more!

When you live in a beautiful area like Idaho, I shouldn’t have any excuses for my morning exercise!! 6km Run ⬇️ 6km Hike ⬆️ Motivation is sometimes a struggle 🤦‍♀️ But staying positive and making it happen, even when it’s hard 💯 Loving my @lifeisgoodco T-shirt… “Not all who wander are lost” and my @strictlywildco hat “Go fast or go home”. Love both these companies (and no they don’t sponsor me, I just like these brands)!

Doing @southernohioforestrally prep while following @officialwrc @rallyitaliasardegna. Great to listen to the wisdom and voices of @becswilliamsrally and WRC Champion Phil Mills. So good to have Phil commentating. Such a legend of our sport!

Can’t wait for the @southernohioforestrally next week with @liakblock @blockhouseracing @43institute @ozrallypro. Lia and I currently lead the @ara_rally National 2wd Championship. We are only 1/2 through the season, so still a long way to go! So proud of how much @liakblock has matured already in our 3 rallies together. I can’t wait to see what’s more to come for the 16 year old  #neverstopimproving @thehoonigans 📸 @joshjsikora

Excited to start reading @mike.a.glover book “Prepared” which will be available to the public June 6th! Mike is the CEO and founder of @fieldcraftsurvival and is former US Army, Special Forces & CIA. Mike is a good friend of @alexgelsomino and I and we are excited to get reading this informative book on survival!

My only fear in life.... is getting a real job. 

Love @alexgelsomino and I get to share our passion for rally. 

#bestjobintheworld @blockhouseracing @43institute @thehoonigans @ozrallypro

Tonight I hosted ladies night at @thecottage1935, our little @airbnb in Horseshoe Bend. We had an incredible night and my new friend @dawn.marie.legatt, gifted me this amazing present ❤️ I love it! Thanks @dawn.marie.legatt #community 💯

It’s rally week!!! You ready @liakblock? Off to the @southernohioforestrally. We have a big battle on our hands this week, with 2020 @ara_rally champions @barry_mckenna97 & @leonjordan1987 joining the 2wd battle! Also Seamus Burke & @martinbrady44 are back. It’s going to be a great 2wd drive field! Can’t wait. @blockhouseracing @43institute @thehoonigans @ozrallypro
Look who we found floating around in Ohio, USA! Great to have you here for the @southernohioforestrally @jaredhudsonrally!

Really cool when walking down the street in Chillicothe, Ohio, to see the @southernohioforestrally banners with @alexgelsomino & @kblock43 from last year and @travispastrana and myself! @blockhouseracing @43institute @thehoonigans @ozrallypro

Usual late recce night! Saturday stages are ready! Next we recce Friday stages and then start racing tomorrow night! @liakblock and I can’t wait to get started @blockhouseracing @43institute @ozrallypro

Many people are asking to see onboards from the  @southernohioforestrally @ara_rally with @liakblock. So here is Stage 15 to enjoy. We were 1st 2WD and 6th Overall in this stage! @blockhouseracing @43institute @thehoonigans @ozrallypro

@alexgelsomino …. I think we should stick to co-driving 🤔🤣🤦‍♀️ Thanks for the fun @razorworldwide. Thanks enough rolls for one day @travispastrana @liakblock 

@blockhouseracing @43institute @ozrallypro

Today was stressful!! My Instagram account of 11 years was hacked from Turkey and closed down!! 

I got messages to my email that my password, email and account had been changed and the account was closed! 

After doing a lot of research and talking to many people, most thought I had no chance and give up! I really only had a 24h chance to fix this! Lucky I was able to sit at my laptop for 10h today and hack the hacker!! They missed one tiny key part, they didn’t change my phone number on the account and it’s how I cracked my way back through. 

I now have new passwords on any account I have and 2 authentication codes. I learnt a lesson to have harder passwords and stricter verifications. 

🖕Hacker!!! Today I win🖕

Awesome to have @dirtfishrally doing end of stage interviews with @josierallies! @liakblock and I loved the challenge of the @southernohioforestrally in the RWD Subaru BRZ and it’s great to see Lia’s excitement here at the end of the fun 8.8mile stage called “America’s Best”! #dirtfishlivecenter @blockhouseracing @43institute @thehoonigans @ozrallypro @kubotausa @toyotires

Good luck to @travispastrana & @liakblock both racing at this weekends @midamerica_outdoors @nitrocross!! Congratulations @liakblock @blockhouseracing! Heat win on her debut in the @nitrocross next car at @midamerica_outdoors!! @43institute @thehoonigans @kubotausa

Excited to partner with @kubotausa and start using these great pieces of equipment at our ranch in Idaho.
We have a lot of maintenance to do year round on our property, from road repairs to upkeeping our UTV track and snow removal. The L2501 Tractor and the SVL65-2 Skid Steer will fit our ranch's needs perfectly.
Stoked to put these awesome machines to work, starting with some road grading to keep us and our neighbors/delivery drivers happy.

#KubotaCountry
#KubotaUSA

Pushed so hard on today’s run to try get a high @whoop score, that while doing hill sprints I got to a Max HR of 197 and had my HR between 90-100% for over 13min. I also nearly 🤮 which wasn’t ideal 🤦‍♀️🤣 Happy to be able to push my body to these levels.

Busy preparing for 2 rallies in the next 2 weeks! First up I have @ara_rally @newenglandforestrally with @liakblock @blockhouseracing and then off to Australia for @motorsportausrally Rally Queensland with @g.dalbo @activrallysport. Then a flat out few weeks of @ozrallypro trainings in Australia and NZ, with over 40 students booked!! #busylittlecodriver 🇺🇸🇦🇺🇳🇿📚📝💯

Back to the @newenglandforestrally for my 10th time. Throw back to 2021 with @travispastrana @subarumotorsportsusa in the famous Concord Pond stage. Concord Pond is one of the gnarliest stages we compete in USA, with a rollercoaster ride through jumps, dips and high speeds. Hang on co-drivers! Looking forward to another great event this week with @liakblock @blockhouseracing @43institute
At @teamoneil ready for testing for the @newenglandforestrally with @liakblock @blockhouseracing!!
Two happy girls. 20miles of testing done at @teamoneil in the Subaru BRZ! @liakblock and I are excited to get started at the @newenglandforestrally @blockhouseracing @43institute @thehoonigans
Always fun testing at @teamoneil! Check out some onboard action with @liakblock and I today! @blockhouseracing @43institute @thehoonigans @kubotausa @ozrallypro
Highlight of today’s recce 🤔 seeing this beauty!!! @liakblock and I hope we don’t see this moose in the rally! She was beautiful 🫎
This is one #happylittlecodriver! I truly love my job 💯 📸 @trevorlydenphoto @blockhouseracing

Rest in Peace Erin Kelly 

The entire USA rally community is in shock. My thoughts go out to TJ and Erin’s husband and family and friends at this shocking time. Erin was such a lovely lady and she will be greatly missed in our tight knit rally community 💔

So happy we were able to capture this photo with Erin in the middle before the start of the New England Forest Rally yesterday. No idea by the end of the day, she would be gone. A sad day in USA rally. RIP ❤️
Life is short ❤️
The rally community is going through another great loss this year. Don’t be afraid to ask for help when needed ❤️ Reach out to others. Talk to people. Don’t do it alone!

Off to Australia 🇦🇺 

Boise - LA - Sydney - Brisbane ✈️

1st Stop - Rally Queensland with @g.dalbo @activrallysport 
2nd Stop - Victoria to see my family 
3rd Stop - @ozrallypro trainings with 24 students in Victoria 
4th Stop - New Zealand for @ozrallypro with 18 co-drivers 

Extremely busy 3 weeks ahead! 

#busylittlecodriver
Airtime with @liakblock at @newenglandforestrally Concord Pond stage! The Subaru BRZ really does fly nice ✈️ @blockhouseracing @thehoonigans @ozrallypro @43institute @kubotausa Great 📸 @zeroto207!!!

Back in my homeland 🇦🇺 for round three of the @motorsportausrally Rally QLD with 21 year old Indonesian driver @g.dalbo! Gande and I did round one together in Tassie and then Gande did @ozrallypro training with @alexgelsomino and myself. I look forward to seeing how much Gande has progressed since our last outing in March @pulangmenang.id  @activrallysport 📸 @wishart_media

Thank you to @subaruaustralia for taking care of me when I am back in Australia. This time I have a lovely Subaru Outback to use while here in Queensland for Rally Queensland! Thanks @blair_read & Clayton Faflik #subaruoutback
Solid test with @g.dalbo today at Rally QLD!!! Now to finish recce and we will be ready for Rally Queensland! @pulangmenang.id @activrallysport
Ready for the start of Rally QLD today with @g.dalbo @pulangkeuttara @activrallysport

Solid first day at Rally Queensland for @g.dalbo @pulangkeuttara and myself! After 8 stages we are 4th in class and 8th overall!! Lots of improvements from @g.dalbo & learning. Looking forward to tomorrows 6 stages. 📸 @aaron_wishart @activrallysport
Keeping an eye on my check in time ⏱️ Day 2 starts in a few hours. 6 stages today! Let’s see what we can do! 📸 @aaron_wishart @g.dalbo @pulangkeuttara @activrallysport

Rally Queensland 
4th Production Cup
7th Overall 
@g.dalbo best result! Thanks to @activrallysport @pulangkeuttara for the support!! 📸 @aaron_wishart

Update Apologies (wrong edit was accidentally posted previously)

Many of you may not have heard my rally stories of survival, from breaking my legs in 9 places in a crash in 2009 to burning my hands and face in a rally fire in 2014, I have been through some crazy experiences, which have lead to me being the strong passionate person I am today. 

Thanks to @blackriflecoffee & @fieldcraftsurvival for telling my story. Give yourself 20min to check out what I have been through to be where I am today. 

Thanks also to @travispastrana & @brendorally., for so much you have achieved with me in the sport in our combined 100 events together. 

Go check it out on Travis’ YouTube: @channel199_ at the link in my bio.

Thanks to Innes Motors Subaru for always taking care of me when I am home visiting my family in Victoria! If you are looking for a Subaru, go see Scott Innes in Bendigo. These outback’s are beautiful cars. @subaruaustralia

If you missed it…. My story of survival is now up! Click the link in my bio @channel199_ ! Thanks to @travispastrana @blackriflecoffee @fieldcraftsurvival @jtarticle15 @mike.a.glover @evanhafer @dovperryribnick for putting my story out for people to be inspired! @subarumotorsportsusa
🤔 Maybe if I chew on my pen hard enough, it will solve all the problems of the world 🤦‍♀️ Thanks for this not so elegant 📸 @aaron_wishart 🤣 Captions 💁‍♀️

I had the fantastic opportunity a few months ago to chat with @priya_richards from @girlsonthegridpod. Part one is now up. Priya is from the legendary Richards family, with her dad being Steve Richards and grandpa Jim Richards. I really enjoyed getting to know Priya more and can’t wait to catch up with her one day!

Something I truly love about @ozrallypro training, is the variety of amazing people we meet along the way. Friday while in Australia, we trained David Bond. David is 71 years old and won the Victorian Rally Championship in the 70s. David has never done a pacenoted rally, so come to train with us and learn the ins and outs of writing pacenotes. David is the oldest driver we have had the privilege to work with since starting Ozrallypro 10 years ago! Thanks for a great day!
Great day of @ozrallypro co-driver with 11 students today in Bendigo, Australia 🇦🇺 at Innes Motors Subaru - @subaruaustralia

Another fantastic day of @ozrallypro training here in 🇦🇺 It was great to work one on one with husband and wife team Carwyn & Carli Harries after the completed the group co-driver training the day before. Today’s focus was on developing precise and accurate Pacenotes. Carwyn is originally from wales and started out rally with the late Gareth Roberts - Jaffa, who I raced in the JWRC. Carwyn now has an Evo 7 which they will compete in the South Australian Rally Championship. All the best to this lovely husband and wife team! #pacenotetraining 📝📚

Nice to be home in Australia 🇦🇺 with family for a few weeks with @ozrallypro trainings. Was great to enjoy a bonfire Saturday night! It’s winter here in Australia, so escaping the hot Idaho summer for a few weeks! 📸 @alexgelsomino #camping #bonfirenight🔥 #australia

On Wednesday DRC 4X4 Motorsport attended @ozrallypro training 🇦🇺 It was great to work one on one with this husband and wife team Darren & Michelle Crozier from Kyneton. Our focus for the training was to develop confidence in their pacenotes, after many years doing blind rallies and away from the sport. Both left with a strong set of skills to take to their next rally in a few weeks time. All the best to this husband and wife team! #pacenotetraining 📝📚 @alexgelsomino

It’s been a hectic few weeks between rallying in USA, Australia, @ozrallypro trainings in Australia 📝 and visiting family. I am now off to New Zealand for the first time since 2019 to train 20 co-drivers. While I head to NZ, @alexgelsomino is off to Finland for a rally! It’s a busy life we live, but we wouldn’t change it for the world 🌎 ✈️

It was great to have the opportunity to train Pete & Chris Schey again yesterday. Pete attended @ozrallypro training in 2018 and Chris in 2021. Since that time, these guys have competed in @dakarrally together and other blind rallies. Yesterday our focus was on preparing these guys for more pacenoted events in 2023. All the best to these brothers! 📸 Photo by Craig O’Brien

Had a great time training this brother and sister team, Braeden & Emma Kendrick. These legends drive this awesome V8 commodore in the Victorian Rally Championship and have also taken it to rounds of the New Zealand Rally Championship. Both had trained with us previously, so this training was about building confidence in their Pacenotes and recce systems. Was great to work with these two again. All the best! @fast_track_towing_n_motorsport
Here in Auckland, New Zealand! Ready for todays @ozrallypro co-driver training @newzealandrallychampionship

A fantastic day in Auckland, NZ training 12 co-drivers! Such great feedback from the day! Thank you Elton Goonan - CEO Motorsport NZ, Blair Bartels & Carl Fenn - @newzealandrallychampionship co-ordinator, Chris Carr - Rally NZ and Fleur Pedersen for your help/support with this @ozrallypro training 📝📚
Everyday you wake up, you have a second chance to do whatever you want, to be whoever you want. The only thing stopping you is YOU!!

Unfortunately we won’t be at @ojibweforestsrally this year, but this rally has given me some of my fondest memories. Here is the first. In 2013, my brother @brendorally and I finished 1st 2WD and 3rd Overall. @kblock43 & @alexgelsomino won the event. My first time standing on the overall podium with both my husband and brother. It was amazing!

@ozrallypro will now be back in Victoria for The Middle of Everywhere Gippsland Rally and is offering one on one training in Wedderburn, Vic August 30 & 31. If you would like to book a day with @alexgelsomino & I, email Ozrallypro@gmail.com.

So excited that my brother @brendorally and my husband @alexgelsomino will be teaming up to do the Gippsland Rally in a couple of weeks!! I will also be competing in the rally with @g.dalbo! This will be my 3rd event in the Australian Rally Championship in 2023 with Gande. Can’t wait! 📸 @aaron_wishart
Thanks to the @loddonherald for always supporting my adventures and reporting back to the locals! Really appreciate it! @alexgelsomino and I had a great week of @ozrallypro  trainings 📝🌎📚🇦🇺
Head to the @girlsonthegridpod to check out my latest podcast with @priya_richards! We recorded these 2 episodes a few months ago and are pumped they are up for all to enjoy!!

If you missed my story of survival by @blackriflecoffee @fieldcraftsurvival click the link in the bio above. They did an incredible job showing what I have been through to be where I am today. Hopefully this inspires people to push their limits, don’t live in fear and never make excuses in life!

7 years ago today, @john_maccrone and I won a round of the Scottish Rally Championship - The Grampian Rally! What an incredible feeling this was. Thanks @rhdmoore for the opportunity to work with you all. John and I competed in 4 SRC rounds together that year and a round of the WRC the following year. Great memories 🌎💯

Happy to be back home in Idaho. Catching up on jobs thanks to @kubotausa. We live on a 3km gravel road in the mountains, which gets very corrugated/washboards in the dry summer months. This @kubotausa box grader has been a great machine to keep the road graded and us and the neighbors happy! #kubotatractor #kubotacountry
My @fordf250oldmate plates arrived this week!

So excited to finally get some proper tyres for my 4 Runner. Thanks to @yokohamatire for my new Geolander X-AT. What a big improvement on the handling and grip on the gravel road to our house #yokohama #yokohamatire

Next up…. @gippsland_rally @motorsportausrally 🇦🇺 with @g.dalbo @pulangmenang.id! This will be @g.dalbo and my 3rd event together in 2023 in the Rally 3 Fiesta. Thanks to @activrallysport for preparing our car. Looking forward to getting back to a rally in my home state of Victoria for the first time since 2019 📸 @aaron_wishart

As a racer and stuntman, Travis Pastrana has always delivered. 

After starting out in motocross, Pastrana became a stunt rider and lead personality behind the Nitro Circus brand, which spans reality TV, movies and live performances. Now, Pastrana is set to become an AMA Motorcycle Hall of Famer. 

In motocross, Pastrana became the then-youngest rider (16 years, 10 months, 26 days) to capture an AMA Pro MX title after winning the 1999 AMA 125cc National MX Championship. He also added the ’01 125cc East SX championship to his resume.

Pastrana then set his eyes on X Games success, where he produced 17 medals, including 11 golds. 

Pastrana also founded and fostered the Nitro Circus brand, which has grown into one of the largest entertainment entities in motor sports. He is also a successful stunt rider, a pursuit sparked by his childhood hero Evel Knievel. 

Pastrana was recognized as the Best Male Action Sports Athlete at the 2007 ESPY Awards, and was the 2018 AMA Motorcyclist of the Year.

#AMAHOF2023 #travispastrana #nitrocircus #stuntrider

Congratulations to 🇺🇸 @rickybrabec, who today won the most grueling rally, the @dakarrally, for the second time!!! To win once, is a dream come true. To win a second time is legend status. It’s hard work, dedication, never give up attitude and mental toughness. @dakarrally is a race of extremes and navigating the most challenging routes in the world and to even fulfill the dream of competing for most, is amazing. It’s an adventure and competition, where people meet the biggest challenge of their life. I was asked to compete this year and I turned it down, as I knew I needed more training and better preparation. I knew I was personally not ready for this challenge. So I truly take my hat off to @rickybrabec! Every year you make 🇺🇸 proud. Toughest rally in the world! You legend! Continue chasing and living that dream 💯
